"title": "7960: singing",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7960: singing",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The musical voicing of praise to God. On account of God's majesty and great acts of salvation singing was a regular part of the life of Israel and of the early church. In Israel musicians and singers were set aside solely for this purpose.</p>\n<h2>The call to sing praise to God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:1-Ps33:3\">PSA 33:1–33:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:1-Ps96:2\">PSA 96:1–96:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:11\">PSA 5:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps9:11\">PSA 9:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps30:4\">PSA 30:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:6\">PSA 47:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:4\">PSA 68:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:32\">PSA 68:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:1-Ps81:2\">PSA 81:1–81:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:1\">PSA 95:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:1\">PSA 98:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:4-Ps98:5\">PSA 98:4–98:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:8-Ps98:9\">PSA 98:8–98:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps117:1\">PSA 117:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:7\">PSA 147:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:1\">PSA 149:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:23\">ISA 44:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:13\">ISA 49:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:9\">ISA 52:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:11\">ROM 15:11</a></p>\n<h2>The resolve to sing praise to God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:33\">PSA 104:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:17\">PSA 7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps9:2\">PSA 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps13:6\">PSA 13:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps57:8-Ps57:9\">PSA 57:8–57:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:16-Ps59:17\">PSA 59:16–59:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:1\">PSA 89:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps101:1\">PSA 101:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:1\">PSA 147:1</a></p>\n<h2>Singing in response to God's deliverance from enemies and sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:10\">ISA 35:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:47-Ps18:49\">PSA 18:47–18:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:22-Ps71:24\">PSA 71:22–71:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:1\">ISA 54:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:12\">ISA 55:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:11-Rev5:14\">REV 5:11–5:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:3-Rev15:4\">REV 15:3–15:4</a></p>\n<h2>God sings of his delight and love for his people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:17\">ZEP 3:17</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Singing in Israel</h2>\n<h3>Singing accompanied major events</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:27-1Chr15:28\">1CH 15:27–15:28</a> <em>the bringing of the ark to Jerusalem</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:12-2Chr5:13\">2CH 5:12–5:13</a> <em>the dedication of the temple</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:21-2Chr20:22\">2CH 20:21–20:22</a> <em>a march into battle</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:11-2Chr23:13\">2CH 23:11–23:13</a> <em>a coronation</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:27-2Chr29:28\">2CH 29:27–29:28</a> <em>the purification of the temple</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:21\">2CH 30:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:15\">2CH 35:15</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:27-Neh12:29\">NEH 12:27–12:29</a> <em>the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem</em></p>\n<h3>Part of day-to-day worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:18\">2CH 23:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh11:23\">NEH 11:23</a></p>\n<h3>Accompanied by instruments</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:16\">1CH 15:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:12\">1KI 10:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:11\">2CH 9:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps137:1-Ps137:4\">PSA 137:1–137:4</a></p>\n<h3>Musicians and singers appointed to lead Israel's singing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:33\">1CH 9:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:22\">1CH 15:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:31-1Chr6:32\">1CH 6:31–6:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:6-1Chr25:7\">1CH 25:6–25:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra2:41\">EZR 2:41</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh7:44\">NEH 7:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra2:65\">EZR 2:65</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh11:22\">NEH 11:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:46\">NEH 12:46</a></p>\n<h2>Singing in the NT</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:19-Eph5:20\">EPH 5:19–5:20</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:13\">JAS 5:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:30\">MAT 26:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:26\">MRK 14:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:25\">ACT 16:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:15\">1CO 14:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:16\">COL 3:16</a></p>\n<h2>Singing is not always appropriate</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:20\">PRO 25:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:5\">ECC 7:5</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:23\">AMO 5:23</a></strong> <em>God detests the songs of Israel that are not accompanied by obedience and justice.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:14-Isa24:17\">ISA 24:14–24:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:5\">ISA 25:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:13\">EZK 26:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos6:5-Amos6:7\">AMO 6:5–6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:3\">AMO 8:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:10\">AMO 8:10</a></p>",
